## 2. Simulation-to-Production Mapping

### Design Rationale
This simulation is a deliberately **miniaturized subset** of the full AURORA production network
(Segment 1 design). Two key deviations are intentional and documented here for the grader:

1. **IP Addressing:** The production design uses `10.10.x.x` (Freiburg HQ). The simulation uses
   `172.16.x.x` to avoid address conflicts with UTM's NAT range (`192.168.64.0/24`) and to
   clearly separate lab traffic from hypervisor management traffic.

2. **SIEM Platform:** The production design specifies Splunk / Microsoft Sentinel (enterprise
   licenses). The simulation uses **Wazuh 4.14.3** as the open-source equivalent, providing
   identical functionality (log collection, indexing, alerting, dashboards) within lab resource
   constraints.

### VLAN Mapping: Simulation → Production

| Simulation VLAN | Simulation Name | Production VLAN (Segment 1) | Production Name | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **30** | MGMT | **30** | IT & Infrastructure | SIEM and management systems live here in both designs |
| **40** | OPERATIONS | **40** | Consulting | Represents the primary user/ops segment |
| **99** | ATTACKER | **51** | Dirty Lab Sandbox | Isolated adversarial zone; VLAN 99 chosen to avoid collision with production IDs |

### VM Inventory → AURORA Network Role

| VM Name | OS | Role in Simulation | Maps to in Production |
|---------|----|--------------------|----------------------|
| **pfSense-Aurora** | pfSense (FreeBSD) | Inter-VLAN Router + Firewall | FortiGate NGFW + Cisco Catalyst 9300L L3 Core |
| **Wazuh-Manager** | Ubuntu 22.04 AMD64 | SIEM (log collection, alerting, dashboard) | Splunk / Sentinel server (VLAN 30) |
| **Switch-1-Alpine** | Alpine 3.23.3 ARM64 | Virtual L2 Switch — Operations segment | Cisco Catalyst 9200L access switch |
| **Switch-2-Alpine** | Alpine 3.23.3 ARM64 | Virtual L2 Switch — Management segment | Cisco Catalyst 9200L access switch |
| **Windows 11 ARM** | Windows 11 Pro ARM64 | Target endpoint with Wazuh agent | Consulting workstation (VLAN 40) |
| **Kali-Linux** | Kali Linux ARM64 | Attacker / penetration tester | Dirty Lab adversarial node (VLAN 51) |

