## 3. VLAN Design & IP Addressing

### IP Scheme Note
Production uses `10.10.x.x`. Simulation uses `172.16.x.x`. The third octet mirrors the VLAN ID
in both schemes (e.g., VLAN 30 → `x.x.30.x`) to keep the mapping intuitive.

### VLAN Scheme

| VLAN ID | Name | IP Subnet | Gateway | Purpose | Production Equivalent |
|---------|------|-----------|---------|---------|----------------------|
| **30** | MGMT | 172.16.30.0/24 | 172.16.30.1 | Management Zone: Wazuh SIEM + Switch-2 | VLAN 30 (10.10.30.0/24) |
| **40** | OPERATIONS | 172.16.40.0/24 | 172.16.40.1 | User Segment: Windows 11 + Switch-1 | VLAN 40 (10.10.40.0/24) |
| **99** | ATTACKER | 172.16.99.0/24 | 172.16.99.1 | Isolated adversarial zone: Kali Linux | VLAN 51 (10.10.51.0/24) |

