## 5. Security Rules & Traffic Flow

### Firewall Rules on pfSense (Inter-VLAN)

#### VLAN 40 (Operations) → VLAN 30 (MGMT)
```
✅ ALLOW: Windows 11 → Wazuh-Manager (TCP 1514, 1515)
✅ ALLOW: Switch-1 → Wazuh-Manager (TCP 1514, 1515)
❌ DENY:  All other traffic to MGMT zone
```

#### VLAN 30 (MGMT) → VLAN 40 (Operations)
```
✅ ALLOW: Wazuh-Manager → All (for agent management)
✅ ALLOW: Switch-2 → All (for network management)
```

#### VLAN 99 (Attacker) → All VLANs
```
❌ DENY:  All traffic by default (isolated)
✅ ALLOW: Manual rules added during penetration testing phases
```

### Expected Traffic Flows

1. **Normal Operations:**
   - Windows 11 → Wazuh (agent heartbeat every 10s)
   - Switch-1 → Wazuh (system logs)
   - Switch-2 → Wazuh (system logs)
   - pfSense → Wazuh (firewall logs via syslog)

2. **Attack Simulation (Segment 4):**
   - Kali → VLAN 40 (port scan, exploit attempts)
   - Wazuh detects suspicious activity
   - Alerts generated in dashboard

